* Three Soroban\nvulnerabilities\n(OpenZeppelin audits)

** 1. Self-recovery inflation\n(Critical, v0.5.0 C-01)
*** RWA token, recovery_address
*** lost_wallet == new_wallet
*** read-read-write on one key\nb + b = 2b
*** bypasses Base::update\n-> total_supply untouched
*** no auth -> repeat (A, A)\n-> b, 2b, 4b, 8b ...
*** Fix: route through\nforced_transfer -> Base::update\n+ identity-continuity check

** 2. Signer aliasing\n(Critical, v0.5.0 C-03)
*** Smart accounts,\ned25519 / webauthn verifiers
*** key_data length >= N,\nsilently truncated
*** (verifier, key||junk)\n= a distinct signer identity
*** one real key ->\nmany "signers"
*** one signature satisfies\nan M-of-N threshold
*** Fix: BytesN<32> fixed type,\nexact-length by construction

** 3. approve_for_all\nTTL underflow\n(High, v0.2.0 H-01)
*** NFT, approve_for_all
*** revoke via\nlive_until_ledger = 0
*** u32: 0 - sequence\n-> underflow -> huge TTL\n-> host panic
*** revocation bricked
*** test at ledger seq 0\nnever triggered it
*** Fix: early return\nwhen live_until_ledger == 0

** Cross-cutting lessons
*** Route balance changes\nthrough the canonical update
*** Make invalid states\nunrepresentable (types)
*** Guard every\nledger_target - ledger_now
*** Test at a realistic,\nnon-zero ledger sequence
*** 2 Critical + 1 High,\nall resolved

@endmindmap
